    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the later phase of Vinca style and culture, from the fourth to the third millennia BCE. The style differs from the earlier Vinca-Tordos particularly in its evolution of sleek, stylized figures decorated with incised lines and abstract patterns.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Se refiere a la última fase del estilo y cultura Vinca, desde el cuarto al tercer milenio a.C. El estilo difiere particularmente del anterior Vinca-Tordos en el desarrollo de figuras bruñidas y estilizadas decoradas con líneas incisas y modelos abstractos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar de latere fase van de Vinca stijl en cultuur, van het 4de tot het 3de millennium v. Chr. De stijl verschilt vooral van de vroegere Vinca-Tordos-stijl door de ontwikkeling van gestroomlijnde, gestileerde beelden, gedecoreerd met ingekerfde lijnen en abstracte patronen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指稱於西元前第4個千禧年至第3個千禧年間發展之文卡風格與文化的晚期階段。此種風格與早期的文卡─托爾多斯文化的不同之處，在於其發展出以鋸齒狀線條和抽象圖案所裝飾而成、線條流暢表面平滑的人形塑像。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
